Text.Value: I know you and Wyll have been getting close, by the way. I owe him a lot, but I don't owe him you.
They're still zipping around inside me.
No permanent damage. And absolutely worth it.
You can count on it.
I miss the feeling of you already.
Oh, this is clever. Might even work. C'mere.

Text.Value: I don't mind sharing you with the bookworm while I'm indisposed, by the way. I'm sure he can keep you entertained until I'm more... approachable.
Believe me, it's my top priority.
I know I can't have much more than that - not until we've found a more permanent solution to the hellfire issue.
You're the only one for me, Karlach. Believe me.
You have your fun with the angry alien 'til then - I don't mind sharing. But keep a piece left over for me, hmm?
Let's just take things as they come.
I'm waiting!

EditorData.NodeContext: Said musically, with excitement and impatience

Text.Value: Have your fun, but save some for me, all right? I won't be too hot to touch for long.
I'd believe you if you said one plus one is seven.
I hope that's true. 'Cause I'm hoping for seconds, thirds, and fourths, once we find a way to cool off this engine.
That's the only way to take 'em, isn't it?

EditorData.NodeContext: REsponse to 'let's just take things as they come'

Text.Value: I know you and hairdo girl have something happening, but keep a piece left over for me, hmm? I won't always be too hot to touch.
Mmm. I'm dizzy. And you - are you all right?
Mine too. Soon enough, you're going to be mine. But until then, I'll play nice.
We'll have to see where we are by then.
I saw sparks - actual sparks.
Gods, me too. That was... amazing. But it is what it is, isn't it? I may not be able to have any fun, but you're still free as a lark.
You have your fun with the pretty boy 'til then - I don't mind sharing. But keep a piece left over for me, hmm?
I will, then.

EditorData.NodeContext: As in, 'I will count on it'.

Text.Value: Very coy. But don't worry - we are nothing if not free, and until I'm back to my full splendour, I make no claims upon you.
Oh, this is clever. Might even work. C'mere.

You have no one but yourself - and Zariel - to blame.
